annotationA: Synaptosomal-associated protein 29kDa; SNAP receptor activity; SNARE binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: vesicle-mediated transport; autophagic vacuole fusion; autophagic vacuole maturation; neurotransmitter secretion
annotationB: Putative Achaete Scute Target (Past1) is a protein that associates predominantly with the plasma membrane and genetically interacts with N. Past1 contributes to endocytosis, male sterility, temperature sensitivity, life span and differentiation of photoreceptors R1/R6/R7 and cone cells; Belongs to the TRAFAC class dynamin-like GTPase superfamily. Dynamin/Fzo/YdjA family
